sql:
SELECT title
FROM publications
WHERE collection_id = (SELECT collection_id FROM collections WHERE collection_name = 'Mathematics');

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_publications
FROM publications
WHERE category_id = (SELECT category_id FROM categories WHERE category_name = 'Mathematics');

external_knowledge:
Relevant knowledge to enhance understanding:

- Categories and collections are used to organize publications; 
- Access count per user signifies how many times a user has accessed a particular publication; 
- Average distinct publications across all groups gives an idea of the diversity of publications being accessed.
